<TEXT>
* REFEREE Steve Dunn, at the centre of the controversial turning-point
of Bolton's play-off victory over Wolves on Wednesday night, yesterday
declared he was right to allow John McGinlay to stay on the field and
score the clinching goal.
The Scot appeared to throw a punch at Wolves striker David Kelly when
Bolton were leading by the forward's first goal. But referee Dunn merely
cautioned both players for the skirmish -- freeing McGinlay to go on and
score the goal that took Bolton through to a Wembley final with Reading
on May 29.
</TEXT>
