* A MEMORIAL plaque to St Bernard's, who won the Scottish Cup 100
years ago, will be unveiled at a ceremony in Edinburgh tomorrow.
Players and supporters are invited to gather at eleven o'clock at Eyre
Place, entrance to the King George V Memorial Park, where the turnstiles
used to stand at the Gymnasium Ground. St Bernard's first played there
in 1880 and it was the site of their last match, in 1942, before the
club folded.
