<TEXT>
* ALLAN Lamb and Kevin Curran both chalked up unbeaten centuries as
Britannic Assurance County Championship leaders Northamptonshire
recovered from a shaky start to take control against Surrey at the
County Ground yesterday.
And defending champions Warwickshire also carved out a strong position
to spoil the opening-day party at Durham's Chester-le-Street stadium,
which was staging championship cricket for the first time.
Veteran Surrey seamer Tony Pigott took two wickets in as many overs to
leave Northants reeling at 101 for four -- but Lamb and Curran guided
them to 363 without further loss by the close.
Skipper Lamb, who was 150 not out, reached his hundred in 203 minutes
off 158 balls with sixteen 4s while Curran, unbeaten on 111, took 215
minutes and 202 deliveries to reach the milestone, which included 18
boundaries.
</TEXT>
