<HEADLINE>Jordan ready to 'strike'</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>47</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321555</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HAMILTON striker Peter Duffield could be set for a #200,000 move to
Bristol City. Manager Joe Jordan had Duffield screened last week during
Accies' 0-0 draw with Raith Rovers at Firhill and the former Hearts
manager is poised to make an offer as he prepares to take his club back
out of the second division.
City managed to net only 42 goals in 46 league games this season --
the second worst record in the first division -- and that lack of
strike-power sent them down.
Hamilton manager Iain Munro paid out just #35,000 to sign 26-year-old
Duffield from Sheffield United in September, 1993, and he has rattled in
44 goals over two seasons.
Partick Thistle have also been linked with the Middlesbrough-born
striker, but Duffield has made it clear he would prefer to return to
England.
However, Jordan may still face competition from fellow second division
club Rotherham, who also had a scout at Firhill.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
