<TEXT>
* Iain Munro has won his appeal against a #200 fine by the SFA.
Munro was censured and fined by the general purposes committee for his
comments following a game against Stranraer earlier this year. He had
been upset at more than 60 fouls being awarded during the game and had
suggested that more protection had to be given to the players.
But Munro stressed that he was not criticising any person, and that he
was attempting to back the SFA's call for fair play.
