<TEXT>
US Open champion Ernie Els and Brad Faxon were paired together
yesterday in the first round of the Buick Westchester Classic, with
Faxon leading the tournament at three under par and Els a stroke behind
as they started their final hole of the day, the par five ninth, writes
Robinson Holloway.
A few minutes later, as they checked their scorecards, Els was the
leader at three under and Faxon was fuming while signing for a 9 on that
last hole. Faxon made a double bogey on the hole, but was given a
two-stroke penalty for hitting the wrong ball.
Els' lead held up for almost the entire round, until little known
American Doug Martin eagled the eighteenth to move to four under par 67,
one stroke ahead of Els and four others.
Nick Faldo, who enjoys this course and whose game should suit it
perfectly, shot a one under par round of 70 to finish two strokes off
the lead. Leading scorers:
