<HEADLINE>Suffolk sheep on display at Thainstone</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321571</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MINI Highland Show of Suffolk sheep will be on display at the
North-east Suffolk Club's ambitious first-time competition at Thainstone
Agricultural Centre, Inverurie, on Saturday, June 10.
As most British quality Suffolk breeders farm in the North-east many
prime animals will be on show before the Highland Show and the main
Suffolk sales in July at Stoneleigh and Edinburgh.
Club chairman Harry Emslie Jr said that the sponsorship of #1400 has
been obtained for prizes in the 10 classes (clipped and unclipped) for
pedigree breeders and four classes for commercial lamb producers, two on
the hoof and two on the hook.
There will be trophies for the champion and reserve and engraved
glasses for class prizes. The main sponsors are J Bibby Agriculture
Limited. Subsidiary sponsors are Intervet and Sherrat Farm Supplies.
Two former Suffolk breeders are judges -- Arnott Barron and Sam
Forrest. The commercial judge is Inverurie butcher Sandy Mitchell.
Entries close on Thursday, June 1, with Suffolk club secretary Fiona
Bruce, Tillyeve Cottage, Udny, Aberdeenshire. Telephone 01651 842616.
</TEXT>
