<DOCID>GH950519-000028</DOCID>
<DATE>950519</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Wallets plan</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321572</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Annan-based market firm of Thomson Roddick &amp; Laurie has put
forward proposals for a 50/50 merger with the Castle Douglas market
company Wallets Marts.
Thomson Roddick &amp; Laurie director John Thomson has said that an
amicable alliance between the two would provide a strong auction and
land agency business based in the south-west of Scotland.
Wallets is already the subject of a #1m takeover bid by James Craig of
Ayr, but shareholders have been advised by the board to make no response
to that offer.
Closer working with Harrison &amp; Hetherington of Carlisle has also been
considered as a possible way forward.
</TEXT>
