<DOCID>GH950519-000031</DOCID>
<DATE>950519</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Hewden Stuart pay</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321575</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DIRECTORS' emoluments soared 40% at Glasgow-based plant hire giant
Hewden Stuart last year to a total of #932,000.
Retiring chairman Sir Matthew Goodwin had his package increased by 43%
to #168,777 which included a discretionary bonus of #70,000.
The highest-paid director, believed to be incoming chairman and former
chief executive Sandy Findlay, saw his remuneration jump 37% to
#184,467, including commission of #71,057, while his successor as chief
executive Alastair Deakin benefited from #509,000 of profit on
exercising options as well as salary of between #145,000 and #150,000.
Last year, group pre-tax profits jumped 82% to #34.8m.
</TEXT>
