<TEXT>
DOES anyone in Scotland, England, Ireland, and Wales understand what
Malcolm Rifkind meant when he said that he had no problems about the
principle of devolution or of constitutional change if there were
proposals which could apply throughout the United Kingdom and create a
stable constitutional structure?
One thing, however, is clear: Mr Rifkind is not going to commit
himself one way or the other.
Daniel McNicol,
43 Castleton Drive,
Newton Mearns.
