<TEXT>
* A new recruitment campaign has been launched to address the critical
shortage of Gaelic teachers.
A careers package has been prepared by Gaelic development agency
Comunn na Gaidhlig in association with the Scottish Office education
department and will be distributed throughout schools, colleges,
universities, and careers events.
Until the end of the century, CNAG estimates 35 new Gaelic primary
teachers will be needed annually to cater for even a modest growth in
students of the language. Ten years ago there were no Gaelic schools.
There are now 47.
</TEXT>
