<TEXT>
* A Sutherland woman is being flooded with phone-calls congratulating
her conquest of Everest -- in fact, the highest Mrs Kath Ballard has
been is 1217ft up Ben Bhraggie behind her home in Seaforth Road,
Golspie.
The problem has arisen because Mrs Ballard's husband, John, is the
only J. Ballard in the Highlands and Islands directory. Mrs Alison
Hargreaves, who became the first woman to climb Everest unaided and
without oxygen, is married to photographer Mr Jim Ballard, of Spean
Bridge, and they are not listed in the telephone directory.
</TEXT>
