<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321637</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
* Two senior Grampian Police officers returned to Aberdeen last night
after an unsuccessful attempt to speak to the protesters occupying the
Brent Spar.
The protesters have now spent almost three weeks on board the
redundant tanker-loading terminal 118 miles north-east of Shetland.
Superintendent Mike Tucker and Inspector Harry Ord, of the offshore
industries liaison unit, flew yesterday to the nearby Brent Alpha
platform, but Greenpeace refused them permission to land on the Brent
Spar. The officers were also unable to arrange a face-to-face meeting on
a vessel.
A spokesman said the purpose of the visit had been to make those on
Brent Spar fully aware of the situation regarding the civil proceedings
which Shell is taking.
</TEXT>
