<TEXT>
Meanwhile, Scotland's new councils are being encouraged to share
expertise and facilities up to an annual value of #25,000, without
having to carry out competitive tendering, writes JOHN McCALMAN.
The relaxation of Government rules is designed to mitigate an
''unintended'' surge in costs that would arise from the extension of
compulsory competitive tendering to the provision of professional
services.
Mr Kynoch said the exemptions would allow an authority to carry out
work for another body, without the CCT rules applying, where the annual
value of the work is less than #25,000.
