<DATE>950519</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Elderly widow killed in bungalow blaze</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>978321659</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AN ELDERLY widow died yesterday when fire swept through her home.
Mrs Helen Brownlee, 78, lived alone in the bungalow in Dunbar Street,
Lossiemouth.
A neighbour raised the alarm early yesterday morning. Mrs Brownlee's
niece, Mrs Sandra Thomson, who lives next door, rushed out to the scene,
where she was joined by other relatives and neighbours.
Nine firefighting appliances attended the scene. Such was the
intensity of the blaze, firefighters were still damping down the embers
seven hours later.
The victim's cousin, Mr Donald Stewart, a retired Strathclyde
University lecturer, said: ''I live near-by but when I got there the
roof had already fallen in. The flames were incredible. No-one could do
anything to save her.''
Mrs Brownlee, who had been awaiting a heart operation, moved back to
her home town 17 years ago when her husband, Willie, died.
The couple had lived in Bishopbriggs, where they regularly attended
Kenmure Kirk.
0 An investigation has been launched to establish the cause of the
blaze.
</TEXT>
