<TEXT>
BEIJING: The President of the Board of Trade, Mr Michael Heseltine,
making the first visit to China by a Cabinet Minister for two years,
announced that commercial deals worth more than #1bn had been pushed
higher in Shanghai.
Britain now tops the list of European investors in China with pledged
funds of #3.4bn. ''I think we can build on this,'' said Mr Heseltine,
who is leading a 130-strong business delegation. Prime Minister Li Peng
told him he hoped the trade mission marked a turning-point in strained
relations between Britain and China over Hong Kong.
